sql:
SELECT name, production_budget
FROM movies
WHERE holiday_release = 1 AND production_budget > 100000000;

external_knowledge:
- Estimated weekly earnings formula: ((total_gross - opening_gross) / opening_screens) * 7.5; 
- Holiday or summer period release refers to a specific time of the year, such as Christmas or summer vacation; 
- MPAA ratings 'PG-13' and 'R' indicate the level of content in the movie; 
- The production budget refers to the cost of producing the movie.

sql:
SELECT AVG(production_budget) AS avg_budget
FROM movies
WHERE holiday_release = 1;
